    <h1>The Patent System's<br><em>Crowdsourcing Window</em></h1>
    <p class="lead">A Third-Party Preissuance Submission (3PPS) is a statutory mechanism that allows any member of the public to place prior art directly in front of a USPTO examiner — before a patent is granted. The window is narrow. The rules are strict. This site explains both.</p>
    <div class="btn-group">
